While the UX Server is positioned as an intermediary similarly to the UDDI Proxy described in our DUDE framework, it focuses more on the QoS framework and does not attempt to implement a seamless federation mechanism such as our DHT based approach.
Although our current implementation focuses on UDDI version 2, in future we will consider semantic extensions to UDDI, WS-Discovery [16] and other Grid computing standards such as Monitoring and Discovery Service (MDS) [10].
In [21], the authors describe a UDDI extension (UX) system that launches a federated query only if locally found results are not adequate.
